1%2525205_10a%252520Twin%252520Cracks.jpg'),(27295,NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-62_LuQRWOmc/UamsrVRU3pI/AAAAAAACPNs/rTElnE5g5h8/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252002%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Nic%252520Leading%252520P2.jpg','Nic leading P2. Fairly straightforward, about 5.7-5.8. Watch the loose blocks though.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-05-26 - 02 - Center Route - Nic Leading P2.jpg',NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-62_LuQRWOmc/UamsrVRU3pI/AAAAAAACPNs/rTElnE5g5h8/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252002%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Nic%252520Leading%252520P2.jpg'),(27296,NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-aADNlGXkAE4/UamsukA1jJI/AAAAAAACPN4/hkwZXQ8uo8U/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252005%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Headwall%252520above%252520the%252520ledge.jpg','Headwall above the ledge. You can see the flaring OW/roof split by a crack on the right. That was our reference for hitting the 5.9+ traverse into the next corner system.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-05-26 - 05 - Center Route - Headwall above the ledge.jpg',NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-aADNlGXkAE4/UamsukA1jJI/AAAAAAACPN4/hkwZXQ8uo8U/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252005%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Headwall%252520above%252520the%252520ledge.jpg'),(27297,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-0VE0vZkkuNU/Uamsv5RR3lI/AAAAAAACPN8/9UBe796Z9vk/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252006%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Nic%252520belaying%252520from%252520ledge%252520below%252520the%252520roof.jpg','Nic belaying from ledge below the roof. You can see the pillar around his corner to the right. Really, if you belay here, you should stop before the corner he is in for the drag. I set up a different belay to correct that.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-05-26 - 06 - Center Route - Nic belaying from ledge below the roof.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-0VE0vZkkuNU/Uamsv5RR3lI/AAAAAAACPN8/9UBe796Z9vk/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252006%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Nic%252520belaying%252520from%252520ledge%252520below%252520the%252520roof.jpg'),(27298,NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-drdWHtJ4jKs/UamsxIszBUI/AAAAAAACPOE/z3knnbIkD-I/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252007%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Traversing%252520around%252520the%252520pillar.jpg','Traversing around the pillar. It sounds like you should climb the pillar, and then do the 5.9+ traverse from there. However, traversing around it might have a technically harder section, but it is cleaner, better protected, and more straight up.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-05-26 - 07 - Center Route - Traversing around the pillar.jpg',NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-drdWHtJ4jKs/UamsxIszBUI/AAAAAAACPOE/z3knnbIkD-I/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252007%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Traversing%252520around%252520the%252520pillar.jpg'),(27299,NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-witAiaDxw0c/UamsyAM2DyI/AAAAAAACPOI/FTL-7kuNEns/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252008%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520P3%252520heading%252520up%252520flake%252520%252526%252520corner%252520after%252520traversing%252520below%252520pillar.jpg','Alternate to the pillar (which Nic zigged back to before zagging back up and right). This left flake is maybe 5.9 to 5.10a, with a thin stepover into the corner. The corner crack has a lot of loose crap (would clean up with more climbing), but it took pro well and was a lot of fun! Crux is the exit, which is a 5.10 flaring finger crack or step around with a mantel finish.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-05-26 - 08 - Center Route - P3 heading up flake & corner after traversing below pillar.jpg',NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-witAiaDxw0c/UamsyAM2DyI/AAAAAAACPOI/FTL-7kuNEns/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252008%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520P3%252520heading%252520up%252520flake%252520%252526%252520corner%252520after%252520traversing%252520below%252520pillar.jpg'),(27300,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-f_I8IFGKHvw/UamsyinitjI/AAAAAAACPOM/X7VwqaQBgFM/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252009%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Nic%252520atop%252520P3.jpg','Nic atop P3. Things were going well, but about to slow down . . .',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-05-26 - 09 - Center Route - Nic atop P3.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-f_I8IFGKHvw/UamsyinitjI/AAAAAAACPOM/X7VwqaQBgFM/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252009%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Nic%252520atop%252520P3.jpg'),(27301,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-qY2-w_O-QoQ/Uams0QdnGAI/AAAAAAACPOY/-vwq3a2e8jk/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252011%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Nic%252520leading%252520P4.jpg','Looking up P4. It is still unclear where to go. Nic started left and stepped right (you could step right to start) to climb the center crack. He reached an impasse higher up, but it might be the way to go and very tough! He tensioned to the right crack (no go) and then to the left crack, which he climbed higher up. The finish is an OW or runout face move, and it is unclear if you can still reach the corner system from the ledge it deposits you on.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-05-26 - 11 - Center Route - Nic leading P4.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-qY2-w_O-QoQ/Uams0QdnGAI/AAAAAAACPOY/-vwq3a2e8jk/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252011%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Nic%252520leading%252520P4.jpg'),(27302,NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Gm56JUloo20/Uams2ZfdfcI/AAAAAAACPOk/oMcPK6jGmmA/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252013a%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Nic%252520leading%252520P4.jpg','Looking up P4. It is still unclear where to go. These cracks were rounded and flaring enough that solid jams and pro were tough to come by. Nic is faced with an OW or runout roof/face move to finish, but the ledge above might be off route. Things weren\'t going well, it was really cold in the shade, and we were only halfway up the wall, behind schedule, and unsure if the route got easier to follow above, so I called it and we bailed.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-05-26 - 13a - Center Route - Nic leading P4.jpg',NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Gm56JUloo20/Uams2ZfdfcI/AAAAAAACPOk/oMcPK6jGmmA/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252013a%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Nic%252520leading%252520P4.jpg'),(27303,NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-sbSz_vXL3Y4/Uams4FL5UvI/AAAAAAACPOw/2peXX_ckgUw/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252015a%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Back%252520at%252520Camp%252520-%252520Nic.jpg','Back at camp. It was so cold in the shade, if only we could be in the sun! Mt Morgan South is behind. (by Nic Risser)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-05-26 - 15a - Center Route - Back at Camp - Nic.jpg',NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-sbSz_vXL3Y4/Uams4FL5UvI/AAAAAAACPOw/2peXX_ckgUw/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252015a%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Back%252520at%252520Camp%252520-%252520Nic.jpg'),(27304,NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-S8qrDlM7Ve4/Uams8MAS9II/AAAAAAACPPM/YYHGsVf0sqE/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252015g%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Nap%252520Time%252520-%252520Nic.jpg','Nap time. (by Nic Risser)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-05-26 - 15g - Center Route - Nap Time - Nic.jpg',NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-S8qrDlM7Ve4/Uams8MAS9II/AAAAAAACPPM/YYHGsVf0sqE/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252015g%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520-%252520Nap%252520Time%252520-%252520Nic.jpg'),(27305,NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-qnV1LEc4cbI/Uams5Uw51dI/AAAAAAACPO8/9WRb5DmFnow/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252015c%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520Rage%252520-%252520Nic.jpg','Nic expressing his feelings to the Center Route. (by Nic Risser)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-05-26 - 15c - Center Route Rage - Nic.jpg',NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-qnV1LEc4cbI/Uams5Uw51dI/AAAAAAACPO8/9WRb5DmFnow/s800/2013-05-26%252520-%25252015c%252520-%252520Center%252520Route%252520Rage%252520-%252520Nic.jpg'),(27306,NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-s7UIaM1CwpM/Ua97v24QWSI/AAAAAAACQh8/eIRp5gOu9sQ/s800/2013-05-25%252520-%25252029%252520-%252520Nic%252520nearing%252520Camp%252520at%25252012%25252C200%252520ft%252520-%252520annotated%252520-%252520L%252520East%252520Arete.jpg','The Left East Arete, as we climbed it. Rating is as encountered and differs from Secor.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-05-25 - 29 - Nic nearing Camp at 12%25252C200 ft - annotated - L East Arete.jpg',NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-s7UIaM1CwpM/Ua97v24QWSI/AAAAAAACQh8/eIRp5gOu9sQ/s800/2013-05-25%252520-%25252029%252520-%252520Nic%252520nearing%252520Camp%252520at%25252012%25252C200%252520ft%252520-%252520annotated%252520-%252520L%252520East%252520Arete.jpg'),(27307,NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-3-Arjeu44b4/Uam3QrQRjhI/AAAAAAACPUg/RNIvS3kl5ac/s800/2013-05-27%252520-%25252002%252520-%252520Left%252520East%252520Arete%252520-%252520Nic%252520Leading%252520P1.jpg','Nic leading P1, at the wide corner crux.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-05-27 - 02 - Left East Arete - Nic Leading P1.jpg',NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-3-Arjeu44b4/Uam3QrQRjhI/AAAAAAACPUg/RNIvS3kl5ac/s800/2013-05-27%252520-%25252002%252520-%252520Left%252520East%252520Arete%252520-%252520Nic%252520Leading%252520P1.jpg'),(27308,NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-CqEeMjhAbRw/Uam3VxDGUyI/AAAAAAACPUw/uy7jR9Yu6Bw/s800/2013-05-27%252520-%25252006%252520-%252520Left%252520East%252520Arete%252520-%252520Looking%252520down%252520P2%252520chimney.jpg','Looking down the P2 chimney. I hand hauled my back up this and then stepped right to continue on easy terrain. The chimney  itself has no pro except the entry and exit and a midway point where you could step right (harder). Nic could follow well with his pack by