00/2013-07-28%252520-%252520070%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_1961.jpg'),(28080,NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-gYQDcyW5g0M/Uhb2jWN7HQI/AAAAAAACfL4/rO7x1Q3XTNk/s800/2013-07-28%252520-%252520073%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_1965.jpg','Following P5, an excellent 5.8 crack!',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-07-28 - 073 - Gimli - IMG_1965.jpg',NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-gYQDcyW5g0M/Uhb2jWN7HQI/AAAAAAACfL4/rO7x1Q3XTNk/s800/2013-07-28%252520-%252520073%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_1965.jpg'),(28081,NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-fSQn5PO5_DA/Uhb2lGRFfsI/AAAAAAACfMA/C3vgLnfAI7U/s800/2013-07-28%252520-%252520074%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_1966.jpg','The \'crux\' roof looms above on P6. Originally rated 5.8, this route\'s rating was bumped to 5.10a due to this. Alec offered me the lead, so off I went! Very easy climbing up into the roof, where I had to figure out how to make the big step left.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-07-28 - 074 - Gimli - IMG_1966.jpg',NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-fSQn5PO5_DA/Uhb2lGRFfsI/AAAAAAACfMA/C3vgLnfAI7U/s800/2013-07-28%252520-%252520074%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_1966.jpg'),(28082,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-d3_8vqWRZ6M/Uhb2s7xEjmI/AAAAAAACfMg/GHvpdCZAz3g/s800/2013-07-28%252520-%252520076aa%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_0315%252520-%252520Alec.jpg','Mark leading the crux pitch (5.9+) of the South ridge. (by Alec LaLonde)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-07-28 - 076aa - Gimli - IMG_0315 - Alec.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-d3_8vqWRZ6M/Uhb2s7xEjmI/AAAAAAACfMg/GHvpdCZAz3g/s800/2013-07-28%252520-%252520076aa%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_0315%252520-%252520Alec.jpg'),(28083,NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-dIbpnqiBrz8/Uhb2uf698dI/AAAAAAACfMo/qowO18y1n04/s800/2013-07-28%252520-%252520077%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_1969.jpg','Alec leading P6 to finish the route. Basically cl. 4 apart from the short 5.7 step that he was on, then it eases back into class 3 and then class 2. I\'d recommend halfing the rope and simul-climbing to the summit for this pitch.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-07-28 - 077 - Gimli - IMG_1969.jpg',NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-dIbpnqiBrz8/Uhb2uf698dI/AAAAAAACfMo/qowO18y1n04/s800/2013-07-28%252520-%252520077%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_1969.jpg'),(28084,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-av4pPFnz2B0/Uhb2xht59hI/AAAAAAACfM4/QtBgnwK3zBI/s800/2013-07-28%252520-%252520079%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_1971.jpg','The easy \'scramble\' to the false summit, the main summit lies beyond. I read that it was cl. 3-4 getting over there . . . but it was only cl. 2!',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-07-28 - 079 - Gimli - IMG_1971.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-av4pPFnz2B0/Uhb2xht59hI/AAAAAAACfM4/QtBgnwK3zBI/s800/2013-07-28%252520-%252520079%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_1971.jpg'),(28085,NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-uHp0iA4GSqk/Uhb2zUNAhOI/AAAAAAACfNA/2SHdmzLcnj8/s800/2013-07-28%252520-%252520080%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_1972.jpg','Asgard Peak seen from the summit of Gimli Peak.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-07-28 - 080 - Gimli - IMG_1972.jpg',NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-uHp0iA4GSqk/Uhb2zUNAhOI/AAAAAAACfNA/2SHdmzLcnj8/s800/2013-07-28%252520-%252520080%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_1972.jpg'),(28086,NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/--YjHWNeWm64/Uhb22-Yz29I/AAAAAAACfNQ/qc8k9sdewSE/s800/2013-07-28%252520-%252520081%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_1973.jpg','Gladsheim Peak seen from the summit of Gimli Peak.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-07-28 - 081 - Gimli - IMG_1973.jpg',NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/--YjHWNeWm64/Uhb22-Yz29I/AAAAAAACfNQ/qc8k9sdewSE/s800/2013-07-28%252520-%252520081%252520-%252520Gimli%252520-%252520IMG_1973.jpg'),(28087,NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-83thLPXqaTE/Uhb240fixqI/AAAAAAACfNY/CD