/-inEkozi3NGE/TjFZCivXcSI/AAAAAAAAkDY/OsthY6T1wWg/s800/7-16-05-20-SeaHorseClouds.jpg'),(29547,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-U_AauoZWBB8/TjFZPxhh-3I/AAAAAAAAkEA/c98b4XrtizI/s800/7-16-05-27-BuckMtn.jpg','Buck Mountain seen from the base of the Golden Staircase on the Grand Teton\'s Exum Ridge.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'7-16-05-27-BuckMtn.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-U_AauoZWBB8/TjFZPxhh-3I/AAAAAAAAkEA/c98b4XrtizI/s800/7-16-05-27-BuckMtn.jpg'),(29548,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Il6MQPrVWp8/TjFZGw9lTZI/AAAAAAAAkDo/90dme_heXZ4/s800/7-16-05-23-LookingDownStepAround.jpg','Ever wonder what it looks like below the Step-Around on Wall Street? Well, now you know!',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'7-16-05-23-LookingDownStepAround.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Il6MQPrVWp8/TjFZGw9lTZI/AAAAAAAAkDo/90dme_heXZ4/s800/7-16-05-23-LookingDownStepAround.jpg'),(29549,NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-EvVFhzUkv0U/TjFZRkXdLvI/AAAAAAAAkEE/Jj0CeDg7M6M/s800/7-16-05-28-WindTunnel.jpg','The rather mediocre pitch known as the Wind Tunnel. Its really just a set of bouldering problems, although the climbing was still fun! From the large ledge above the Golden Staircase, Joe and I free-climbed over to the boulder-filled chute to the right.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'7-16-05-28-WindTunnel.jpg',NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-EvVFhzUkv0U/TjFZRkXdLvI/AAAAAAAAkEE/Jj0CeDg7M6M/s800/7-16-05-28-WindTunnel.jpg'),(29550,NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-vTruDYs-nWo/TjFZimYFiEI/AAAAAAAAkEs/zf00ZvlwuPY/s800/7-16-05-38-FrictionPitch%2520Bypass.jpg','Above the Wind Tunnel we coiled our ropes and free-soloed up to a notch to the right, and back around to the left to reach this spot. Climb up the cracks on the left for a fun full pitch to reach the small Boulder Ledge at the base of the Friction Pitch - the crux of the Upper Exum Ridge. To avoid this pitch, you can also ascend the gulley to the right (often iced over, as it is in the photo), or ascend the chimney in the center corner (5.6-5.7).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'7-16-05-38-FrictionPitch Bypass.jpg',NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-vTruDYs-nWo/TjFZimYFiEI/AAAAAAAAkEs/zf00ZvlwuPY/s800/7-16-05-38-FrictionPitch%2520Bypass.jpg'),(29551,NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-8eiSsN90KgY/TjFZseYsQ3I/AAAAAAAAkFA/2ZSOK4wtkBc/s800/7-16-05-43-FrictionPitch.jpg','The Friction Pitch seen from Boulder Ledge. It was a little hard to follow the route description along here - but if you see rock like this, you\'re definitely on route! Climb up the groove to the right (takes a bit of pro), and double back left to two black knobs before launching up the pitch.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'7-16-05-43-FrictionPitch.jpg',NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-8eiSsN90KgY/TjFZseYsQ3I/AAAAAAAAkFA/2ZSOK4wtkBc/s800/7-16-05-43-FrictionPitch.jpg'),(29552,NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-1S67GOMN0rk/TjFZ18lqjoI/AAAAAAAAkFU/4139I6de3Ds/s800/7-16-05-48-LookingDownFrictionPitch.jpg','My view down the Upper Exum Ridge as I neared the top of the Friction Pitch.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'7-16-05-48-LookingDownFrictionPitch.jpg',NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-1S67GOMN0rk/TjFZ18lqjoI/AAAAAAAAkFU/4139I6de3Ds/s800/7-16-05-48-LookingDownFrictionPitch.jpg'),(29553,NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-ymn54RFiWHc/TjFZ5obfJtI/AAAAAAAAkFc/xE15cyFp_XI/s800/7-16-05-50-JoeAtTop%2520of%2520FrictionPitch.jpg','Joe Bullough at the top of the Friction Pitch on the Upper Exum Ridge.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'7-16-05-50-JoeAtTop of FrictionPitch.jpg',NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-ymn54RFiWHc/TjFZ5obfJtI/AAAAAAAAkFc/xE15cyFp_XI/s800/7-16-05-50-JoeAtTop%2520of%2520FrictionPitch.jpg'),(29554,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-AcPve6fwtW8/TjFZ9VrL7EI/AAAAAAAAkFk/KI36NkO_EmY/s800/7-16-05-52-Notch%2526V-Pitch.jpg','From the top of the Friction Pitch, we coiled our ropes again and free-soloed past an exposed notch (left), up a short headwall (right), and around the east side (right) of the ridge to reach the V-Pitch (aka. Open Book Pitch). This pitch is the slanting dihedral illuminated by the sun in the upper left of the photo.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'7-16-05-52-Notch&V-Pitch.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-AcPve6fwtW8/TjFZ9VrL7EI/AAAAAAAAkFk/KI36NkO_EmY/s800/7-16-05-52-Notch%2526V-Pitch.jpg'),(29555,NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-KbCW6lMmfQk/TjFZ_T1tcxI/AAAAAAAAkFo/sKF8yTixyrE/s800/7-16-05-53-JoeFlyinHigh.jpg','Joe Bullough living the high life near the top of the Upper Exum Ridge.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'7-16-05-53-JoeFlyinHigh.jpg',NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-KbCW6lMmfQk/TjFZ_T1tcxI/AAAAAAAAkFo/sKF8yTixyrE/s800/7-16-05-53-JoeFlyinHigh.jpg'),(29556,NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-TC95wACmP9I/TjFaPZxi4AI/AAAAAAAAkGM/98Y0Mz-DoPM/s800/7-16-05-57-EastRidge.jpg','The huge monolith below is the large gendarme on the East Ridge, seen just past Beckey\'s Couloir. The round lake just to the left of this feature is Amphiteater Lake, a popular hiking destination that offers incredible views of the Grand Teton, and access to its northern face. To the left is Delta Lake, and to the right in the valley are Bradley Lake and Taggart Lake. Disappointment Peak is hidden behind the gendarme.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'7-16-05-57-EastRidge.jpg',NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-TC95wACmP9I/TjFaPZxi4AI/AAAAAAAAkGM/98Y0Mz-DoPM/s800/7-16-05-57-EastRidge.jpg'),(29557,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-V0wtQktPY0g/TjFaG_gp4xI/AAAAAAAAkF4/25EQJ0blmho/s800/7-16-05-61-V-PitchFromNotch.jpg','Looking up at the V-Pitch from the notch above the Friction Pitch. The \"V\" is the slanting dihedral in the top center of the photo.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'7-16-05-61-V-PitchFromNotch.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-V0wtQktPY0g/TjFaG_gp4xI/AAAAAAAAkF4/25EQJ0blmho/s800/7-16-05-61-V-PitchFromNotch.jpg'),(29558,NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/