TRI/PxVVt5z-QpQ/s800/2006%2520-%25205-31%2520-%2520Ruth%2520004%2520-%2520Clouds.jpg','Mt Dan Beard and the Don Sheldon Mountain Hut seen through a parting in the storm that had us socked in for several days on the Ruth Glacier. This photo was taken at around midnight.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2006 - 5-31 - Ruth 004 - Clouds.jpg',NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-AQtzs_-zOcc/ThQe88G_cfI/AAAAAAAATRI/PxVVt5z-QpQ/s800/2006%2520-%25205-31%2520-%2520Ruth%2520004%2520-%2520Clouds.jpg'),(30128,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-EVMWc0yitRI/ThQe9_hu_pI/AAAAAAAATRQ/4b8NX-Nbi_M/s800/2006%2520-%25205-31%2520-%2520Ruth%2520005%2520-%2520Clouds%2520%2526%2520Flags.jpg','A sign of our multi-storm abating, we could see the alpenglow light up Mt Dan Beard through a parting in the clouds. Ironically, the best view of the scene was taken from the camp\'s latrine area.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2006 - 5-31 - Ruth 005 - Clouds & Flags.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-EVMWc0yitRI/ThQe9_hu_pI/AAAAAAAATRQ/4b8NX-Nbi_M/s800/2006%2520-%25205-31%2520-%2520Ruth%2520005%2520-%2520Clouds%2520%2526%2520Flags.jpg'),(30129,NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-tmQCkYUoS40/ThQfBdGlCEI/AAAAAAAATRo/crGaygEmAIY/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520002%2520-%2520The%2520Trench.jpg','A few more ways to pass time at camp . . . passing through the trench when wandering around camp! I carried out my architectural vision and expanded the hole into an L-shaped 8\'X 8\' trench with a stepped entrance on one side (good for walking in and out) and a steep wall on the other (good for falling in or climbing out). When we circled camp on the way to the latrine, while flossing, etc. we would add the trench to the loop.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2006 - 6-01 - Ruth 002 - The Trench.jpg',NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-tmQCkYUoS40/ThQfBdGlCEI/AAAAAAAATRo/crGaygEmAIY/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520002%2520-%2520The%2520Trench.jpg'),(30130,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-AEAZ9I8wioo/ThQh-YYEUGI/AAAAAAAATfM/UsmTmkxzVIY/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520043%2520-%2520BIG%2520Avvy%2520on%2520Barrille%2520-%2520Composite.jpg','Avalanche sequence on Mt Barille',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2006 - 6-01 - Ruth 043 - BIG Avvy on Barrille - Composite.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-AEAZ9I8wioo/ThQh-YYEUGI/AAAAAAAATfM/UsmTmkxzVIY/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520043%2520-%2520BIG%2520Avvy%2520on%2520Barrille%2520-%2520Composite.jpg'),(30131,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-70ytzNPqm38/ThQflPchxYI/AAAAAAAATUU/uqPZvh8Cqpc/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520021%2520-%2520Skiier.jpg','Michael Buchanan catching some turns beneath a late evening sun (ca. 8pm). The peak behind him is Pk. 7,580, which is a crap chute that poured rocks and muddy avalanches continously down its deep gulleys the entire time we were on the Ruth.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2006 - 6-01 - Ruth 021 - Skiier.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-70ytzNPqm38/ThQflPchxYI/AAAAAAAATUU/uqPZvh8Cqpc/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520021%2520-%2520Skiier.jpg'),(30132,NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-1yvddsEukuU/ThQfmv6ZCzI/AAAAAAAATUc/XqzhMVVGN2M/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520022%2520-%2520Buchanan%2520Skiing.jpg','Michael Buchanan catching some great skiing on the slopes above our camp on our last day on the Ruth Glacier. Behind him you can see the Rooster Comb (left), and of course, Denali.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2006 - 6-01 - Ruth 022 - Buchanan Skiing.jpg',NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-1yvddsEukuU/ThQfmv6ZCzI/AAAAAAAATUc/XqzhMVVGN2M/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520022%2520-%2520Buchanan%2520Skiing.jpg'),(30133,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-oxfVtsuqrSI/ThQh5Nj52LI/AAAAAAAATe8/HW0-CoDuzbs/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520026%2520-%2520Trench%2520Climbing%2520-%2520The%2520Happy%2520Trench.jpg','Heathfield and Buchanan climbing out of the \"happy\" trench that I dug next to our campsite. Not only could we practice climbing crap snow, but by setting skiis over the trench we could do pullups. Additionally, by hanging a pulley for crevasse rescue from the skiis, we could string a weighted pack in the trench through the pulley to a shovel handle with our climbing rope, allowing us to do any gym exercise that uses a pulley (rows, bicep curl, torso twists, etc.)!',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2006 - 6-01 - Ruth 026 - Trench Climbing - The Happy Trench.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-oxfVtsuqrSI/ThQh5Nj52LI/AAAAAAAATe8/HW0-CoDuzbs/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520026%2520-%2520Trench%2520Climbing%2520-%2520The%2520Happy%2520Trench.jpg'),(30134,NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-yRZ9WbwyAOE/ThQgZyFlYVI/AAAAAAAATYY/vWQlXmoP4pI/s800/2006%2520-%25206-02%2520-%2520Ruth%2520006%2520-%2520Avvy%2520on%2520Crap%2520Pile.jpg','An avalanche on Pk. 7,580 that split into two streams on the face. This was a rare sight as the peak has so many deep gorges that we could only see slides on this face pouring out onto the debris piles at its base.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2006 - 6-02 - Ruth 006 - Avvy on Crap Pile.jpg',NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-yRZ9WbwyAOE/ThQgZyFlYVI/AAAAAAAATYY/vWQlXmoP4pI/s800/2006%2520-%25206-02%2520-%2520Ruth%2520006%2520-%2520Avvy%2520on%2520Crap%2520Pile.jpg'),(30135,NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-qpaibolUq5w/ThQf6SJ991I/AAAAAAAATWQ/ZYNKbhprZkA/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520036%2520-%2520Avvy%2520on%2520Barrille.jpg','Some of the many avalanches that poured off of Mt Barrille this day.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2006 - 6-01 - Ruth 036 - Avvy on Barrille.jpg',NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-qpaibolUq5w/ThQf6SJ991I/AAAAAAAATWQ/ZYNKbhprZkA/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520036%2520-%2520Avvy%2520on%2520Barrille.jpg'),(30136,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-4-Y7DMbR8YM/ThQf4Tv4j5I/AAAAAAAATWI/-gQmpY83_gA/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520035%2520-%2520Avvy%2520on%2520Dicky.jpg','An avalanche streaming off of Mt Dickey.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2006 - 6-01 - Ruth 035 - Avvy on Dicky.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-4-Y7DMbR8YM/ThQf4Tv4j5I/AAAAAAAATWI/-gQmpY83_gA/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520035%2520-%2520Avvy%2520on%2520Dicky.jpg'),(30137,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-J1F4HRxPHI4/ThQgJLdxlRI/AAAAAAAATXI/CgZBQK77Mvw/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520043%2520-%2520BIG%2520Avvy%2520on%2520Barrille.jpg','A large slide off of the NW slopes of Mt Barrille caused by a collapsing cornice. We expected the avalanche activity to really pick up as the temperatures cooled with the evening hours. Heathfield, Buchanan, and I dug out seats in the snow to watch the show, and we weren\'t disappointed. This was the largest of perhaps 20 separate slides that we saw come down in the area over about an hour\'s time. Sadly, despite Heathfield\'s wishes for Buchanan and my baptisms in flying powder, we didn\'t get powderblasted by any of the slides. For scale, that slide was about 150-200 feet wide.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2006 - 6-01 - Ruth 043 - BIG Avvy on Barrille.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-J1F4HRxPHI4/ThQgJLdxlRI/AAAAAAAATXI/CgZBQK77Mvw/s800/2006%2520-%25206-01%2520-%2520Ruth%2520043%2520-%2520BIG%2520Avvy%2520on%2520Barrille.jpg'),(30138,NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-_4y3JNHBRLs/ThQgP0wftCI/AAAAAAAATXs/Ipmc7q4rGVk/s800/2006%2520-%25206-02%2520-%2520Ruth%2520001%2520-%25202am%2520sunset%252C%2520Explorer%2520Peak.jpg','This alpenglow above Explorer Peak was about the only sign of a setting/rising sun at around 2am. It immediately started to get lighter again!',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2006 - 6-02 - Ruth 001 - 2am sunset%252C Explorer Peak.jpg',NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-_4y3JNHBRLs/ThQgP0wftCI/AAAAAAAATXs/Ipmc7q4rGVk/s800/2006%2520-%25206-02%2520-%25