%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3149.jpg','Looking down P2. The upper sections wasn\'t wide, but it was still somewhat burly and tricky. I couldn\'t help but stand on a loose chockstone, which I accidentally kicked down as I started the next pitch.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-09-23 - 042 - Isosceles Pk W Face - IMG_3149.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-2sAzn0B--tw/UkPDplrUbMI/AAAAAAACyCY/gIy40qtHzxs/s800/2013-09-23%252520-%252520042%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3149.jpg'),(30564,NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-JfeR2VE-Hgk/UkPDkpaOx2I/AAAAAAACyCQ/aYIOpMxLG5c/s800/2013-09-23%252520-%252520041%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3148.jpg','I belayed Jared up P2 from the little alcove at the base of the OW that begins P3. It turned out to be a lot tougher and steeper than it looked. To me it seemed harder than Pratt\'s Crack.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-09-23 - 041 - Isosceles Pk W Face - IMG_3148.jpg',NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-JfeR2VE-Hgk/UkPDkpaOx2I/AAAAAAACyCQ/aYIOpMxLG5c/s800/2013-09-23%252520-%252520041%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3148.jpg'),(30565,NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-5R8YaAWhJj0/UkPDyPoLlwI/AAAAAAACyCo/W36qW6YSzso/s800/2013-09-23%252520-%252520044%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3151.jpg','Looking down the OW for P3. This one wasn\'t as technically difficult as the first one, but I was gassed, so I plugged in and rested more. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-09-23 - 044 - Isosceles Pk W Face - IMG_3151.jpg',NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-5R8YaAWhJj0/UkPDyPoLlwI/AAAAAAACyCo/W36qW6YSzso/s800/2013-09-23%252520-%252520044%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3151.jpg'),(30566,NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-YRNnN7Uc5Fw/UkPD0YoM3jI/AAAAAAACyCw/f133x-FQ18Q/s800/2013-09-23%252520-%252520045%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3152.jpg','Looking up more wide for P3 if we had continued up. It was getting dark, so we needed to get off! I stepped right into blocky terrain to speed things up. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-09-23 - 045 - Isosceles Pk W Face - IMG_3152.jpg',NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-YRNnN7Uc5Fw/UkPD0YoM3jI/AAAAAAACyCw/f133x-FQ18Q/s800/2013-09-23%252520-%252520045%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3152.jpg'),(30567,NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-KwLdFP1_4HQ/UkPD3uTnW8I/AAAAAAACyC4/DKe5qxg0C-M/s800/2013-09-23%252520-%252520046%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3153.jpg','Mt Winchell seen after sunset. The W Arete that we had hoped to climb is prominent. Another time! ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-09-23 - 046 - Isosceles Pk W Face - IMG_3153.jpg',NULL,'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-KwLdFP1_4HQ/UkPD3uTnW8I/AAAAAAACyC4/DKe5qxg0C-M/s800/2013-09-23%252520-%252520046%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3153.jpg'),(30568,NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-rFJvvphshZg/UkPD7AVU-xI/AAAAAAACyDA/AqmjE6KcuWk/s800/2013-09-23%252520-%252520047%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3154.jpg','Looking up from the top of our P3 deviation. From here we continued up and right to intersect the SW Buttress Route. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-09-23 - 047 - Isosceles Pk W Face - IMG_3154.jpg',NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-rFJvvphshZg/UkPD7AVU-xI/AAAAAAACyDA/AqmjE6KcuWk/s800/2013-09-23%252520-%252520047%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3154.jpg'),(30569,NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-14DZapkjX7g/UkPENLqcA1I/AAAAAAACyDo/wZnscKI7NiE/s800/2013-09-24%252520-%252520052%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3159.jpg','Mt Winchell seen from camp. The SW Ridge that we had hoped to climb is the sinuous line profiled in shadow on the left. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-09-24 - 052 - Isosceles Pk W Face - IMG_3159.jpg',NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-14DZapkjX7g/UkPENLqcA1I/AAAAAAACyDo/wZnscKI7NiE/s800/2013-09-24%252520-%252520052%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3159.jpg'),(30570,NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Y6QLTlReoSo/UkPEVDfXvyI/AAAAAAACyD4/3akZYEkKvTI/s800/2013-09-24%252520-%252520053a%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3160.jpg','The western flanks of the Palisades seen from Dusy Basin. This palisade is continuously 1,000\'-2,000\' high.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-09-24 - 053a - Isosceles Pk W Face - IMG_3160.jpg',NULL,'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Y6QLTlReoSo/UkPEVDfXvyI/AAAAAAACyD4/3akZYEkKvTI/s800/2013-09-24%252520-%252520053a%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3160.jpg'),(30571,NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-WdF2qHoHWKQ/UkPEdMM2AoI/AAAAAAACyEM/eE5ICov0au0/s800/2013-09-24%252520-%252520054a%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3161.jpg','The jumble of aretes rising up to Starlight Peak and North Palisade. There are two interesting buttresses on N Palisade, the West Buttress (IV, 5.10) and Southwest Buttress (IV, 5.11c OW) ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2013-09-24 - 054a - Isosceles Pk W Face - IMG_3161.jpg',NULL,'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-WdF2qHoHWKQ/UkPEdMM2AoI/AAAAAAACyEM/eE5ICov0au0/s800/2013-09-24%252520-%252520054a%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3161.jpg'),(30572,NULL,'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-1Y44_462UOk/UkUZsRnB6JI/AAAAAAACx_Q/Tzhgmt-lNy0/s800/2013-09-23%252520-%252520018%252520-%252520Isosceles%252520Pk%252520W%252520Face%252520-%252520IMG_3124%252520-%252520annotated.jpg','Iscosceles Peak seen from camp. The West Face route that we woul